      <description>&lt;p&gt;A limit order book is a fundamental concept in market microstructure that shows the quantity of securities being bid or offered at various price levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;key-components&#34;&gt;Key Components&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bid side: Orders to buy at specific prices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ask side: Orders to sell at specific prices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spread: Difference between best bid and ask prices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;market-impact&#34;&gt;Market Impact&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding limit order books helps traders:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gauge market depth and liquidity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze price impact of trades&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop effective execution strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
